Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Directive 90/675/EEC of December 1990 laying down the principles governing  the organization of veterinary checks on products entering the Community from third countries  (1),  as amended by Directive 91/496/EEC  (2), and in particular Article 30 thereof,
Having regard to Council Directive 91/496/EEC of 15 July 1991 laying down the principles governing  the organization of veterinary checks on animals entering the Community from third countries and  amending Directives 89/662/EEC, 90/425/EEC and 90/675/EEC, as amended by Directive 91/628/EEC  (3),  and in particular Article 28 thereof,
Whereas Commission Decision 92/430/EEC  (4) draws up a list of border inspection posts preselected  for veterinary checks on products from third countries;
Whereas Commission Decision 92/431/EEC  (5) draws up a list of border inspection posts preselected  for veterinary checks on animals from third countries;
Whereas some Member States proposed new border inspection posts to be included on the  abovementioned lists in accordance with the provisions of Article 9 (3) of Directive 90/675/EEC and  Article 6 (3) of Directive 91/496/EEC;
Whereas Decisions 92/430/EEC and 92/431/EEC must be amended accordingly;
Whereas the measures provided for by this Decision are in accordance with the opinion of the  Standing Veterinary Committee,
